The Nigeria Immigration Service, NIS, on Friday, advised all shortlisted candidates for the CDCFIB Computer-Based Aptitude Test to start checking their email addresses/phones for their Exam Centres notifications as from midday. It also wished all shortlisted candidates good luck as they prepare for the Computer Based Aptitude Test (CBAT). NIS made the announcement in a tweet via its Twitter handle on Friday. “PUBLIC NOTICE,” NIS tweeted. “All shortlisted candidates for the CDCFIB Computer-Based Aptitude Test are advised to start checking their email addresses/phones for their Exam Centres notifications as from Midday today. Good luck.” DAILY POST recalls that the Federal Government (FG) through the Ministry of Interior, had on Monday, provided an update on the ongoing recruitment into the Nigeria Immigration Service (NIS) and the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC). The Ministry informed the general public that the CBAT for recruitment into the NIS would hold on December 7. It also stated that the CBAT for the recruitment for the NSCDC would hold on December 8 across all the 36 States, including the Federal Capital Territory (FCT).<img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-857709" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/NIS.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="167" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/NIS.jpg 600w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/NIS-300x84.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px">